Definition at line 5 of file BDO.h.

Member Function Documentation

- (id) init  

Initializes the class. Used for objects which do not load themselves from the database, but that still load other records.

Definition at line 9 of file BDO.m.

- (id) initWithIdentifier: (NSNumber *)  ident  

Initializes the class with a numeric identifier identifying the record in the database. Intended to be used by objects that load themselves from the database only.

Reimplemented in Entry, OS, and Section.

Definition at line 9 of file BDO.h.

- (BOOL) isGhost [read, write, assign]

Whether or not the object has been loaded into memory. Should be YES if it's still in the database, or NO if it's been loaded into memory.
